description:
Union Home Minister Amit Shah on Tuesday will release the Bharatiya Janata Party's manifesto in Lucknow for the upcoming Uttar Pradesh Assembly elections. The release of the manifesto 'Lok Kalyan Sankalp Patra' was earlier postponed after Lata Mangeshkar's demise.
Meanehile, Prime Minister Narendra Modi will be addressing virtual rallies in Uttarakhand, Uttar Pradesh and Punjab. His virtual rally in Punjabâ€™s Ludhiana and Fatehgarh Sahib, will be his first in the state. The elections to five states kicks off with the first phase of polling in UP on February 10. Stay with Indiatoday.in for all the latest updates.
